s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Sarah Zuercher\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23094:\"\n<p>Our calendar products are trusted in a wide variety of industries. Seeing The Events Calendar in different contexts shows the versatility and depth of our products.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Today, we’re showcasing how <a href=\"https://evergreenchamberorch.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Evergreen Chamber Orchestra</a> uses our products to manage their calendar and ticketing. We’ll show you the details of how Evergreen Chamber Orchestra combines <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Events Calendar Pro</a> and <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets Plus</a> to create an effective events calendar, including how they sell both virtual and in-person tickets for their events. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-the-homepage\">The homepage</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When you navigate to their homepage, you’re greeted with a vibrant design. You’ll see the blue button to <strong>View All Events</strong>, which will take you to the events page. The menu also brings you to the events page under <strong>Get Tickets</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-kadence-image kb-image2546969_61a3e5-37 size-full\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"3456\" height=\"1424\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"kb-img wp-image-2546973\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1.png 3456w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-300x124.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-665x274.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-140x58.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-768x316.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-1536x633.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-2048x844.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-430x177.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-645x266.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-2000x824.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-1068x440.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-460x190.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-1602x660.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-1074x443.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-512x211.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-1611x664.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-707x291.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-600x247.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.19.33 AM-1-500x206.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 3456px) 100vw, 3456px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Scrolling down, you’ll find the events calendar embedded directly on the homepage. The events are listed chronologically, with details such as date, time, title, location, ticket type (virtual, in-person, or hybrid), description, and cost.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-kadence-image kb-image2546969_330238-35 size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"3456\" height=\"1614\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"kb-img wp-image-2546974\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM.png 3456w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-300x140.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-665x311.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-140x65.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-768x359.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-1536x717.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-2048x956.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-430x201.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-645x301.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-2000x934.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-1068x499.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-460x215.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-1602x748.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-1074x502.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-512x239.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-1611x752.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-707x330.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-600x280.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-10.25.55 AM-500x234.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 3456px) 100vw, 3456px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-the-main-events-page\">The main events page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>At the top of the main events page, there is a featured header picturing the 2024-2025 season. Underneath the image, they promote virtual events, letting users know that all tickets include the livestream and replay of the performance.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-kadence-image kb-image2546969_8927ff-72 size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"2196\" height=\"1148\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"kb-img wp-image-2546975\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM.png 2196w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-300x157.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-665x348.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-140x73.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-768x401.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-1536x803.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-2048x1071.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-430x225.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-645x337.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-2000x1046.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-1068x558.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-460x240.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-1602x837.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-1074x561.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-512x268.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-1611x842.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-707x370.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-600x314.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.06.39 PM-500x261.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2196px) 100vw, 2196px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The default view for events is the <strong>list view</strong>, but you can easily toggle to <strong>month view </strong>or <strong>day view</strong>. The<strong> list view</strong> gives you plenty of information about the event before selecting a single events page. You can also see that each event is labeled as in-person, hybrid, or virtual. Additionally, the price range of each event is listed, so you know what to expect before selecting an event.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-kadence-image kb-image2546969_69ec80-f0 size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1360\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"kb-img wp-image-2546976\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM.png 1360w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-272x300.png 272w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-665x733.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-77x85.png 77w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-768x847.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-430x474.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-645x711.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-1068x1178.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-460x507.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-1074x1185.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-512x565.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-999x1102.png 999w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-481x530.png 481w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-600x662.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.09.28 PM-500x551.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-the-single-events-page\">The single events page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>After clicking on an event, you’ll go to the single events page, where there is a title, date, time, cost, and description of the event. There are also ticketing options, since Evergreen Chamber Orchestra uses Event Tickets Plus. They have two ticket options for this specific event: adult ($40) and child ($20). You’ll see that under each ticket is the amount of tickets remaining. When you set up your ticket on the backend, you can choose the quantity of tickets available.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-kadence-image kb-image2546969_968dd2-5e size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1032\" height=\"1614\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"kb-img wp-image-2546977\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM.png 1032w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM-192x300.png 192w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM-655x1024.png 655w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM-54x85.png 54w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM-768x1201.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM-982x1536.png 982w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM-430x673.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM-645x1009.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM-460x719.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM-512x800.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM-705x1102.png 705w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM-339x530.png 339w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-10-at-1.48.37 PM-500x782.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1032px) 100vw, 1032px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Underneath the description of the event, you’ll find the program, listing out the songs featured in the performance. Given the nature of the event, this is a helpful addition, offering attendees a preview of the show and what they can expect.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-kadence-image kb-image2546969_785f15-75 size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1400\" height=\"1582\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"kb-img wp-image-2546978\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM.png 1400w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-265x300.png 265w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-665x751.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-75x85.png 75w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-768x868.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-1359x1536.png 1359w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-430x486.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-645x729.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-1068x1207.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-460x520.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-1074x1214.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-512x579.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-975x1102.png 975w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-469x530.png 469w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-600x678.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-12-at-2.00.34 PM-500x565.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-the-virtual-events-page\">The virtual events page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Events Calendar Pro</a>, you can <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/creating-a-virtual-event/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">create virtual or hybrid events</a>. The event will look identical to other events, but is set up differently on the backend. You can add a video URL to the event and select who has access to it:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>You can show your content to “everyone” regardless of whether they have registered for your event or signed in.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can select the “logged in” option if you’d only like your registered users to see your content.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>If you have Event Tickets, then you can opt to only allow users who have an RSVP or ticket to see the content (which is how Evergreen Chamber Orchestra operates!)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>When looking at their virtual events page, you can see that they offer unlimited virtual event tickets. Although they charge for virtual events, virtual tickets are “pay what you like.” As you can see, the pricepoint ranges from $20-$80. This model benefits everyone involved: it keeps ticket prices affordable while providing the option for attendees to contribute more if they choose.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-kadence-image kb-image2546969_bee5b5-51 size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1032\" height=\"1614\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"kb-img wp-image-2546979\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM.png 1032w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM-192x300.png 192w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM-655x1024.png 655w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM-54x85.png 54w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM-768x1201.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM-982x1536.png 982w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM-430x673.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM-645x1009.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM-460x719.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM-512x800.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM-705x1102.png 705w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM-339x530.png 339w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.00.48 PM-500x782.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1032px) 100vw, 1032px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The virtual events page also provides a description of the event. The program is listed out, providing a detailed song list so that attendees know what to expect.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-kadence-image kb-image2546969_46e6ce-f0 size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1032\" height=\"1614\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"kb-img wp-image-2546980\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM.png 1032w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM-192x300.png 192w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM-655x1024.png 655w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM-54x85.png 54w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM-768x1201.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM-982x1536.png 982w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM-430x673.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM-645x1009.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM-460x719.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM-512x800.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM-705x1102.png 705w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM-339x530.png 339w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/Screenshot-2024-12-06-at-1.01.12 PM-500x782.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1032px) 100vw, 1032px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-this-calendar-and-its-features-are-worth-exploring\">This calendar and its features are worth exploring</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Evergreen Chamber Orchestra offers in-person and virtual events using <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Events Calendar Pro</a> and <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Events Tickets </a><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">P</a><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">lus</a>. They do a wonderful job of sharing their music to everyone who wants to listen, regardless of location. We’re thrilled to see our tools in action and how we’ve helped Evergreen Chamber Orchestra make virtual events a reality.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to create your own events? We’ve got a full suite of plugins available to help with all of your event and ticketing needs (whether in-person, hybrid, or virtual!) Try out any of our plugins today by requesting a <a href=\"https://demo.theeventscalendar.com/request-demo-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">free demo site</a>. We’re excited to have you try our products! Questions during the demo? We’re always here to help. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Contact us!</a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/featured-calendar-evergreen-chamber-orchestra/\">Featured Calendar: Evergreen Chamber Orchestra</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"We’ve Upgraded The Events Calendar and Event Tickets with Onboarding Wizard and Booking Fees\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:163:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/weve-upgraded-the-events-calendar-and-event-tickets-plus/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 17 Dec 2024 19:46:24 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"What\'s New\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2546927\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:641:\"<p>We are excited to announce that The Events Calendar and Event Tickets got upgrades today! We’re here to give you the details. Onboarding Wizard is a streamlined setup tool that helps new users get started quickly with The Events Calendar. Enjoy a guided walkthrough of how to set up your first event.&#160; Booking fees for&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/weve-upgraded-the-events-calendar-and-event-tickets-plus/\">We’ve Upgraded The Events Calendar and Event Tickets with Onboarding Wizard and Booking Fees</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Sarah Zuercher\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11693:\"\n<p>We are excited to announce that The Events Calendar and Event Tickets got upgrades today! We’re here to give you the details.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Onboarding Wizard is a streamlined setup tool that helps new users get started quickly with <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">The Events Calendar</a>. Enjoy a guided walkthrough of how to set up your first event.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Booking fees for <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets</a> is aimed at helping event organizers cover general administration costs. Booking fees enable you to charge an additional fee on top of the ticket price. This is a common practice for event organizers, as booking fees help offset a variety of operational expenses.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get into these updates!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-an-overview-of-the-onboarding-wizard-for-the-events-calendar\">An Overview of the Onboarding Wizard for The Events Calendar</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s start by exploring the Onboarding Wizard. With this guided process, new users can get up and running quickly with The Events Calendar. It provides the tools and information you need to set up your first event.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the Onboarding Wizard, new users can enjoy:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Reduced setup time from hours to minutes</strong>: Save time by this streamlined setup approach.No more searching through multiple tabs—everything you need is right in the WordPress dashboard.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Guidance through the essential first steps</strong>: Provides clarity on how to publish an event and on what information is necessary. It also helps you determine if you need the free version of Event Tickets and walks you through setup.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Flexibility in the setup experience:</strong> Experience a flexible process with the option to skip steps, save your progress, and resume later.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Onboarding Wizard supports new users in their setup process, saving valuable time.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-utilizing-the-onboarding-wizard-for-the-events-calendar\">Utilizing the Onboarding Wizard for The Events Calendar</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To access the Onboarding Wizard, navigate to the admin dashboard and select <strong>Events</strong> → <strong>First Time Setup</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXe7g1ok8_CLUxqx1hoUPLrZv2OYDM7-qMkno7B6X7kmYh5U8krvfi73KTyduuPhTu5BDoyIiww-hnEp_VOUb-iJNSbzrOQZxwA432qgF1ha22bKjXc8sQo6-__eZTbi1bYx8LsYRA?key=DOwQNSS3V75jurRR_akqQAbL\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Onboarding Wizard page will appear. You have the option to either <strong>set up my calendar </strong>or <strong>skip guided setup</strong>. For this runthrough, we are going to set up the calendar. At the bottom of the page, click the checkbox to share basic information and have access to the chatbot.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXeXpOS85siLXuVsdTU-gqrChJVDg_Z4nvi_1OqFhxRtRGkhyb5EdBP_8g8OYBvKNnoEW5cdPNhicd_QLbWye1QYmHYbG3og5o9KQ9xfcA_fJrapae8_JfkMDBdbKqRSxm80LneL?key=DOwQNSS3V75jurRR_akqQAbL\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There are five steps after you start the setup process: display, settings, organizer, venue, and tickets. On the <strong>Display</strong> page, choose how you want to display your calendar.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXcAOHqZePaVJRDvOwtgLGYKASzfuMju5A8wBLYfUsPxg0PvkGOnVkkIiD6QOqlaPGmX9LQ_j0E1Xd8zaCq5XuBmcucFQAulJrNx2HqfuudfrgMPKfaUAcMU5kF46q8QE7QTyVKE4Q?key=DOwQNSS3V75jurRR_akqQAbL\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, on the <strong>Settings</strong> page, select the currency, time zone, date format, and the day your week starts on.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXe43a6vjZ-YrX7wvsamSePJ_N6VWplhaGj9CNOVfnvWWfTOxv9Pqw1W_4Tr1Z_h401nyaR5hWcBy7Qtx1KpNcBEWXTaSMFMMFWJXxltiMQa1qMG1YHM41MQxRpuzMkKzXOboDmSPA?key=DOwQNSS3V75jurRR_akqQAbL\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the <strong>Organizer</strong> page, enter the organizer’s name. You also have the option to add a phone number, website, and email address.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfWgbOlliRVVKFnQxQZoJ83taTlCHZUSIxD7tBIqwWsG8ByNErnx9TOmQzT4euehxLtdjq6dotv9Sbvau-8k-PNynVmsZPSDUI3ujIag0-oAgouluXiQVsoeJW7KRJVxNcRTIpFhg?key=DOwQNSS3V75jurRR_akqQAbL\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Venue</strong> page lists the venue name, address, city, state, zip code, and country. Optionally, you can add a phone number and a website.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXcIhWHsMD6tsCehP4Il-EFcRc9raIsRiz5Qa3p6SIf7AVJ4DJmwGOpa1-wdRXL30qvfkv9gp79MBG3hqIQLPZFiL7deAJx-jmjqWhWWIHaDPyPLWvC-k3W0f8d3csl3WQBLcpYg?key=DOwQNSS3V75jurRR_akqQAbL\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Lastly, on the <strong>Tickets</strong> page, you have the option to install Event Tickets for free, which will be helpful if you are selling tickets or collecting RSVPs.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfhTf6YfQDw4PM-lKK_jR1mlZ7wOqtGHKN0IP23jyxRrAhmRUxixHept75Dexh1-LaLgu3L7xswUmVhY1hdkfOye5WJdUyouo13plxie-GPkAmZeHX1qbNHzj9qk-66B1qsHDk3CQ?key=DOwQNSS3V75jurRR_akqQAbL\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, our new Onboarding Wizard guides you through the entire process of creating an event, helping you learn the right steps. This feature is designed to help new users quickly become familiar with The Events Calendar.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-an-overview-of-booking-fees-for-event-tickets\">An Overview of Booking Fees for Event Tickets</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With this Event Tickets update, you can now add booking fees to your ticket sales, offsetting your general administrative costs. All booking fees can be displayed separately or included in the total price. Additionally, all fees can be customized per event. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s how booking fees can enhance your event planning experience:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Helps separate operational costs from the ticket price, ensuring transparency in cost distribution.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Provides flexibility in revenue collection, accommodating different venue costs. Since each venue has unique overhead expenses, booking fees allow you to cover those fluctuating costs while keeping ticket prices consistent.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Maintains a competitive base ticket price while still covering essential expenses.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Streamlines accounting by distinguishing additional service costs.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Enables revenue sharing with partners and vendors.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, booking fees provide many benefits. Ready to set up your booking fees? Let’s walk through the process together.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-setting-up-booking-fees-with-event-tickets\">Setting up booking fees with Event Tickets</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To access booking fees, navigate to the admin dashboard and select <strong>Tickets</strong> → <strong>Booking Fees</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfNq9OBjyWKISDY2ZZ_2HoaTiozrMVnZiybJHi-XsQ9g58LsDAxaWRhEET2od_hdkkni5nbv1aN_JzJZlHyZC1P-PqmC4_fYaxQlAxaAZfcBxGHRl88DsBjJDmNAYhYVyjvMdKoYA?key=DOwQNSS3V75jurRR_akqQAbL\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Select <strong>Add New</strong> on the top left of the screen. From there, you can add the fee name and set the amount.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXeMIlNrMIIXsM8K3BxjWqj-bgjAx4lXleM2mXnBc4auAZsr1Scfg_mOFzSrV2Vnxua5EPwPguqctjAEfD49ZK1fC_uKzmRjTXzCW8lrk8T5V29eug7oxGyU1gDNGI1337mLn0VuVA?key=DOwQNSS3V75jurRR_akqQAbL\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You have flexibility while adding a fee:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Fee types: percent or flat.</strong> A percent will take a percentage of the cost of the ticket while the flat fee will charge the same dollar amount no matter the cost of the ticket. This provides flexibility for different business models.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Status: Active, inactive, or draft.</strong> You have flexibility in deciding the status of the booking fee, easily switching it from active to inactive, or to a draft if you aren’t finished yet.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Apply Fee to: Set per ticket or all tickets.</strong> You can specify whether the booking fee should be added when a ticket is created, or if it should apply universally to all tickets. This setting provides flexibility based on the types of events you organize.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Hit save when you make your selections. Note that you can make as many booking fees as needed, giving you the freedom to cater a booking fee to specific events or venues.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-using-the-booking-fee-for-a-specific-event-and-ticket\">Using the booking fee for a specific event and ticket</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When adding tickets to an event, you’ll see the “Ticket Fees” section at the bottom of the ticket settings. From there, select which fee you’d like to apply to the corresponding ticket. Hit “Save Ticket” to update your ticket.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXcRpVnFf1ylBD_h9ZquMsT518RTGE7GiXTiTuVmumtDaueT1q617uR6o9UFUWyQ9wwtkYozYtC-Utu3nUkrGCxQlutSBybmhyDbPLAULRJxKcb4-RWc9kyeuk1hXyZP27eutyXS?key=DOwQNSS3V75jurRR_akqQAbL\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the front end, the booking fee will show up at the checkout page. Please note that the name of the booking fee will also be displayed (in this case, the name was “event fee” with a 5% charge.)</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXeooQrlVkHLrapUjxP4FUHGcELrWDGRlmWnmYSyr8NsKMxIzoybBsynxol5grjlokvqkB6iVo6S5ezGCqHHJ53lXKR7VPLCnAkSS5HujSj2m1s-leMF2UT196rteNOtw8vO-j_1VQ?key=DOwQNSS3V75jurRR_akqQAbL\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-with-every-update-we-take-our-products-to-the-next-level\">With every update, we take our products to the next level</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Onboarding Wizard gives new users a guided tutorial, making it easy to begin using The Events Calendar.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Booking fees are a key part of our ongoing efforts to make Event Tickets the best ticketing plugin available. We’re excited that this update offers more ticketing flexibility for our customers and further strengthens the competitiveness of our product. Whether you’re looking to cover the cost of insurance, material preparation, licensing, venue, or marketing costs, booking fees offer the perfect solution. Keep ticket costs competitive while covering the general administrative costs for your event.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’re always evolving our products to help you, our customers, which is why we’re passionate about giving you consistent updates that enhance your experience. Here’s to even more enhancements ahead!</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/weve-upgraded-the-events-calendar-and-event-tickets-plus/\">We’ve Upgraded The Events Calendar and Event Tickets with Onboarding Wizard and Booking Fees</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"Eventbrite Tickets 4.6.16\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:160:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/eventbrite-tickets/eventbrite-tickets-4-6-16/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 17 Dec 2024 19:40:49 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Eventbrite Tickets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2546955\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:582:\"<p>Summary Maintenance Release The latest version of Eventbrite Tickets resolves an issue where the Eventbrite Event Status and Eventbrite Event Privacy options could not be updated after an event was saved. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing. ✅ Fixed Bugs squashed in this&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/eventbrite-tickets/eventbrite-tickets-4-6-16/\">Eventbrite Tickets 4.6.16</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3630:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-1 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">The latest version of Eventbrite Tickets resolves an issue where the Eventbrite Event Status and Eventbrite Event Privacy options could not be updated after an event was saved.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-2 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-fixed\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixed</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Resolved an issue where the Eventbrite Event Status and Eventbrite Event Privacy options could not be updated after an event was saved.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-3 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-tweaks\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Tweaks in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Changed views: `eventbrite/eventbrite-meta-box-extension`</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-4 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>0 new strings added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>90 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>22 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/eventbrite-tickets/eventbrite-tickets-4-6-16/\">Eventbrite Tickets 4.6.16</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"Event Tickets 5.18.0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:150:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets/event-tickets-5-18-0/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 17 Dec 2024 19:40:18 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Event Tickets\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2546946\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:566:\"<p>Summary Feature Release The latest update of Event Tickets introduces Booking Fees, a way to set up Fees for your Tickets being sold through TicketsCommerce. Additionally, new Seating features check out below! Read more about Booking Fees here. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets/event-tickets-5-18-0/\">Event Tickets 5.18.0</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6395:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-5 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-normal-font-size\">Feature Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">The latest update of Event Tickets introduces Booking Fees, a way to set up Fees for your Tickets being sold through TicketsCommerce. Additionally, new Seating features check out below!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Read more about Booking Fees <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/weve-upgraded-the-events-calendar-and-event-tickets-plus/\">here</a>.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\"> testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-6 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-features\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2728.png\" alt=\"✨\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Features</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">New features in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added option to detach assigned seating tickets from layout and revert them to regular tickets.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add support for max ticket purchase limit filter with seating tickets.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Introducing Booking Fees. A way to set up Fees for your Tickets being sold through TicketsCommerce.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-fixes\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixes</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Correctly calculate and set the session expiration date in the seat selection modal.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ensure that number_format is used with a float value to prevent issues with PHP 8.0+.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Hide seating reservation settings when the seating license is not valid. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Order updates for asynchronous payment methods in Stripe will update correctly</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The Attendee Registration page is now compatible with Full Site Editor themes. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Users will not be able to RSVP for unpublished events or posts.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-8 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-tweaks\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Tweaks in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added actions: `tec_tickets_commerce_checkout_cart_before_footer_quantity` * Tweak &#8211; Added filters: `tec_tickets_commerce_prepare_order_for_email_send_email_completed_order`, `tec_tickets_commerce_prepare_order_for_email_send_email_purchase_receipt`, `tec_tickets_commerce_paypal_order_get_unit_data_{$type}`, `tec_tickets_commerce_paypal_order_get_unit_data`, `tec_tickets_commerce_stripe_create_from_cart`, `tec_tickets_commerce_order_modifiers_api_role`, `tec_tickets_commerce_order_modifiers_coupons_enabled`, `tec_tickets_commerce_order_modifiers_repository_class`, `tec_tickets_commerce_order_modifiers_model_class`, `tec_tickets_commerce_order_modifiers_page_url`, `tec_tickets_commerce_order_modifier_display_amount`, `tec_tickets_commerce_order_modifier_generate_slug`, `tec_tickets_commerce_order_modifier_status_display`, `tec_tickets_commerce_order_modifier_types`, `tec_tickets_commerce_order_modifiers`, `tec_tickets_commerce_order_modifier_default_type`, `tec_tickets_commerce_order_modifier_status_flags`, `tec_tickets_commerce_single_orders_items_item_should_be_displayed` </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Changed views: `v2/commerce/checkout/cart/footer`, `v2/commerce/checkout/cart/footer/total`, `v2/commerce/checkout/order-modifiers/coupons`, `v2/commerce/checkout/order-modifiers/fees` </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Removed outdated ticket duration tooltips.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>127 new strings added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>353 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>5 obsoleted.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets/event-tickets-5-18-0/\">Event Tickets 5.18.0</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"Event Tickets Plus 6.1.2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:159:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets-plus/event-tickets-plus-6-1-2/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 17 Dec 2024 19:39:49 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Event Tickets Plus\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2546949\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:588:\"<p>Summary Maintenance Release This version of Event Tickets Plus includes fixes for attendee registration fields when the AR modal is disabled and corrected template overrides. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing. ✅ Fixes Bugs squashed in this release: ⚙️ Tweaks Tweaks in this&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets-plus/event-tickets-plus-6-1-2/\">Event Tickets Plus 6.1.2</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4591:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-10 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">This version of Event Tickets Plus includes fixes for attendee registration fields when the AR modal is disabled and corrected template overrides.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-11 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-fixes\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixes</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Attendee registration fields will now appear when the AR modal is disabled.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Corrected all template override paths in `src/admin-views/manual-attendees` files and set `set_template_folder_lookup` to `true`.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ensure that number_format is used with a float value to prevent issues with PHP 8.0+.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Prevent Seating scripts from loading on the Attendee Registration page or Checkout when there are no Seating Tickets in the cart.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Remove an additional `pdf/` being added to the template override path for the files in the `attendee-details` directory.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You will now be correctly forwarded to the attendee registration page when using IAC with the attendee registration modal disabled.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-12 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-tweaks\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Tweaks in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Changed views: `tickets-plus/attendee-list-checkbox-rsvp`, `tickets-plus/attendee-list-checkbox-tickets`, `tickets-plus/orders-edit-meta`, `tickets-wallet-plus/pdf/pass/body/ticket-info/attendee-details` </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated file paths in the folder &#8216;src/views/tickets-plus&#8217; for `attendee-list-checkbox-rsvp.php`, `attendee-list-checkbox-tickets.php`, and `orders-edit-meta.php` from `[your-theme]/tribe` to `[your-theme]/tribe-events`.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-13 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>0 new strings added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>31 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets-plus/event-tickets-plus-6-1-2/\">Event Tickets Plus 6.1.2</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0: