r</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5891:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-22 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-normal-font-size\">Feature Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">The latest update of The Events Calendar introduces a new Onboarding Wizard and First Time Setup admin page for new installs!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Read more about the Onboarding Wizard <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/weve-upgraded-the-events-calendar-and-event-tickets-plus/\">here</a>.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\"> testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-23 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-features\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2728.png\" alt=\"✨\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Features</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">New features in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added a new Onboarding Wizard and First Time Setup admin page for new installs.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-24 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-fixes\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixes</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>When importing events from Google Calendar when using Events Calendar Pro with a custom Google Maps API key, Provinces/States for non-US countries are now saved to the correct field.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>When using &#8220;Move to trash events older than&#8221;, trashed imported events are now ignored.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Changed `format` method to `format_i18n` to allow for translations of dates in the TEC Elementor Widget. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Correct template override path to match docblocks for `event-export` directory.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Correct application of upsell classes on the settings page.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-25 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-tweaks\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Tweaks in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Fix the integration with TEC Tweaks to avoid a fatal error when using the extension.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated the docblock for the tribe_get_previous_events_link, tribe_get_next_event_link, and tribe_get_gridview_link functions.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Improved documentation for the tribe_the_next_event_link, tribe_the_prev_event_link, and tribe_get_events_link functions.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update docblocks in the `Tribe__Events__Importer__File_Importer_Events` class.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added filters: `tec_events_onboarding_wizard_permissions`, `tec_events_onboarding_wizard_handle`, `tec_events_onboarding_wizard_country_list`, `tec_events_onboarding_wizard_timezone_list`, `tec_events_onboarding_wizard_currencies_list`, `tribe_events_onboarding_wizard_initial_data`, `tec_events_admin_notice_event_tickets_should_display`, `tec_events_admin_notice_utc_timezone_should_display`, `tec_events_settings_should_filter_page_logo_source` </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Changed views: `integrations/elementor/widgets/event-export`, `integrations/elementor/widgets/event-export/list-item`</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-26 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>87 new strings added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>156 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 obsoleted.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-9-0/\">The Events Calendar 6.9.0</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"The Ultimate Guide to KPIs for Event ROI\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:137:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/event-metrics/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 11 Dec 2024 16:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Event Management\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2546334\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:549:\"<p>You’ve planned and executed another great event. Or at least you think so – it’s hard to know exactly if you weren’t tracking event metrics as closely as you could have.&#160; An easy way to prevent feeling unsure about the success of your event is to consider metrics at every stage of the event process.&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/event-metrics/\">The Ultimate Guide to KPIs for Event ROI</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Rachel Kolman\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21684:\"\n<p>You’ve planned and executed another great event. Or at least you think so – it’s hard to know exactly if you weren’t tracking event metrics as closely as you could have.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>An easy way to prevent feeling unsure about the success of your event is to consider metrics at every stage of the event process. Event metrics can help you justify your event strategy, evaluate the return on your investment (ROI), and determine the ultimate success of your <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/defining-event-goals-and-objectives/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">goals and objectives</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Crunching the numbers may not be quite as fun as hosting the event, but using the data is incredibly useful—and it’s easier than you think!&nbsp; In this article, we’ll take you through the tried and true key performance indicators (KPIs) that you should be tracking to see your maximum ROI.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>First, we’ll explain why tracking metrics is important. Then, we’ll dive into what you should track and how to measure and report these metrics, including:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"#h-total-registrations-or-tickets-sold-nbsp\">Total registrations or tickets sold</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#h-attendance\">Attendance</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#h-event-engagement-and-participation\">Event engagement and participation</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#h-cost-of-the-event\">Cost of the event</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#h-email-engagement\">Email engagement</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#h-survey-results\">Survey results</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#h-social-media-engagement\">Social media engagement</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#h-website-traffic\">Website traffic</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#h-new-customers-or-partners\">New customers or partners</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#h-total-revenue\">Total revenue</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"#h-testimonials\">Testimonials</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get started!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-why-track-event-metrics-nbsp-nbsp\">Why track event metrics?&nbsp;&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>After any event, you’ll be left with two important questions: Did the event pay off? How so? Tracking event metrics can help you answer these questions and do the following:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Determine if your event was a success.</strong> Creating <a href=\"https://www.kpi.org/kpi-basics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)</a> and comparing actual results to desired results will let you know how your event stacked up to your expectations. </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Inform future events</strong>. Your KPIs can show where you may need to change or improve things for the future. </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Improve the attendee experience. </strong>Gain insight using metrics that understand your event from an attendee’s perspective to improve attendee engagement and enjoyment. </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Show value. </strong>Having a variety of metrics allows you to show your event’s value to a leadership team, sponsors, and the like. With the numbers from your event metrics in hand, you’ll be able to confidently prove that your event was a hit. </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow\">\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow\">\n<p>“There are two sides to every event: the business or resource management side and the attendee experience side. Most KPIs will speak to the business side because those things are easy to measure. Marketing, sales, traffic, etc. These are essential when determining the success of your event from that perspective. On the other side, the attendee experience side, you need qualitative feedback. Which means things like survey responses and testimonials are likely the most important data to collect out of everything. This is where you learn if your event provided value to your attendees or if you missed the mark.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>–Nathan B. Weller, Product Marketing Manager for The Events Calendar </p>\n</blockquote>\n</blockquote>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-event-metrics-to-track-nbsp\">Event metrics to track&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We know there are many, many metrics to consider, and it can be a time consuming process to pay attention to them all. However, you don’t need to track each one if it doesn’t serve you, your event, or your organization. The specific metrics that you&#8217;ll focus on depend on your objectives.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some of the most useful ones to keep an eye on:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-total-registrations-or-tickets-sold-nbsp\">Total registrations or tickets sold&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This event metric shows the number of total folks who signed up for your event or paid for a ticket. You can also track <em>when</em> people register or buy a ticket.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-it-helps\">How it helps</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This number gauges the initial interest folks had in your event. It’ll also give you a starting point for understanding revenue, if you’re selling tickets.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Paying attention to <em>when</em> folks sign up allows you to adjust your marketing plan to focus on peak windows, such as early bird promotions or last-minute ticket releases.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-to-track-this\">How to track this</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>A plugin like Event Tickets can help track your tickets and registrations. With <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets Plus</a>, you can collect attendee information through RSVPs and use this information to start generating reports for this and other important event metrics. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-attendance\">Attendance</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This number is the count of folks who actually came to your event, either in person or virtual.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-it-helps-0\">How it helps</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Your actual attendance can give insight into how successful your promotions have been, how “can’t-miss” your event feels, and the success of your event reminders leading up to the event.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-to-track-this-0\">How to track this</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Tracking actual attendance is easy with <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/event-qr-codes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">QR code check-ins</a>, which is possible with Event Tickets Plus. You can also use our Attendee Report feature to quickly compare total attendee check-ins to total tickets issued. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-event-engagement-and-participation\">Event engagement and participation</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This metric measures how attendees feel and act while at your event and if they take advantage of all that your event has to offer.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-it-helps-1\">How it helps</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Gauging engagement and participation helps you understand how interesting and relevant your event has been to your targeted audience. For example, if you have a high dropout rate during your virtual event, then perhaps the information was not helpful to attendees.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-to-track-this-1\">How to track this</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>You can pay attention to this metric both throughout your event and in follow-up surveys. For example, for virtual events, monitor live chat, polls, time spent on the platform/app, and so on.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>During live events, notice the audience’s interactions with peers and guests/speakers, participation in breakouts/workshops, and the like. After the event, send a survey on the level of engagement and what folks participated in the most to gain some quantifiable data.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-cost-of-the-event\">Cost of the event</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This event metric compares your total cost of the entire event (promotion, speakers, advertising, materials, travel, venue, and more) against your projected budget to get a better idea of your actual spending.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-it-helps-2\">How it helps</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Tallying up your total cost can help clarify a few things. First, it will let you know how off-base (or on the mark) your budget was for this event. It can inform you if you need <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/how-to-get-sponsors-for-your-next-event/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">more sponsorships</a> in the future to cover high-than-expected costs. You can also compare this number to your total revenue to see if your event lost or made money. </p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-to-track-this-nbsp\">How to track this&nbsp;</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s best to track total costs using a budget tracker or template and to fill in actual numbers as they add up. Create a budget spreadsheet with Microsoft Excel or Google Sheets, or consider using a software specifically made for budgeting.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-email-engagement\">Email engagement</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This metric tracks how many folks opened your emails and clicked through to either learn more about your event or to register for your event.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-it-helps-3\">How it helps</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Email engagement gives a glimpse at how well your <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/a-complete-guide-to-email-marketing-for-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">email marketing</a> efforts are working. You can estimate early interest in your event as well. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>After the event, open and clickthrough rates (and unsubscribe rates) can help inform you of the event’s effectiveness and perception.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-to-track-this-2\">How to track this</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Begin with an email marketing tool and connect it to your Events Calendar through <a href=\"https://zapier.com/apps/mailchimp/integrations/the-events-calendar/1168292/create-campaigns-in-mailchimp-for-new-events-in-the-events-calendar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Zapier</a> to automatically create email campaigns for each new event. Additionally, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/promoter/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Promoter</a> from The Events Calendar is made for event email marketing and also provides metrics you can track. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-survey-results\">Survey results</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a questionnaire you can send to your attendees, typically after the event, to gather some more information on the effectiveness of the event from their point of view.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-it-helps-4\">How it helps</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>A survey provides direct feedback (both positive or negative!) about the event that you can use to improve the next one.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As mentioned, surveys can help you see how engaging the event was. You can also ask for more information about the attendees, what they liked the most, and if they would come back.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-to-track-this-3\">How to track this</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This is as simple as creating a survey and sending it out shortly after your event. However, it’s important to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/survey-questions-to-ask-attendees-after-an-event/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ask the right questions</a>. For example, you can ask attendees:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Yes or no questions (Was this your first time attending an event?)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Multiple choice (How many sessions did you attend?)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ranking questions (On a scale of 1-5…)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Demographic info (What is your annual household income?)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Open-ended (What could be improved?)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://www.netpromoter.com/know/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Net Promoter Score (NPS)</a> (How likely are you to recommend our events to a friend?) </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-social-media-engagement\">Social media engagement</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>These are the posts you make across your social media accounts (typically Instagram, X, LinkedIn, and Facebook) about your event and how many comments, likes, and shares the posts receive.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-it-helps-5\">How it helps</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This metric gives insight into what others are saying (or not saying) about the event online. It’ll also show how expansive your reach is and provide another indicator of interest in your event.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-to-track-this-4\">How to track this</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Look at your social media mentions, shares/reposts, comments, DMs, and likes. Most social media sites have built-in metric platforms for tracking performance.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also use <a href=\"https://blog.hootsuite.com/how-to-use-utm-parameters/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">UTM parameters</a>, which are fragments added to URLs that provide insights on link performance. This information helps you see if folks came to your website from one social media platform more than the others. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-website-traffic\">Website traffic</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Web traffic is not just the clicks on your web pages. It also includes new users, engagement time, page views, and conversion rates.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-it-helps-6\">How it helps</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Your overall traffic shows how your event pages are leaving impressions on attendees and partners. It could also indicate a higher interest and increase in your brand awareness.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-to-track-this-5\">How to track this</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Look at your site data in Google Analytics. In Google Analytics, navigate to Reports to find Acquisition and Engagement overviews. These pages can show you data like where your website visitors come from, how long they’re spending on your site, and which pages are most popular.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-new-customers-or-partners\">New customers or partners</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>What new people did you bring to the organization? What alliances or partnerships did you form? This is the metric to track those!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-it-helps-7\">How it helps</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This event metric helps demonstrate your conversion rate and gives information about your bottom line – or your end goal.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, if your event is being held as a way to promote your new product, then ultimately, new customers buying your product is a perfect way to determine if your event was a success.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-to-track-this-nbsp-0\">How to track this&nbsp;</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Track your event leads and follow up with salespeople and your CRM to see who is converting. The Events Calendar <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/hubspot-integration/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">integrates with Hubspot</a> so you can track all of your customer data in one place. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, talk to new partners directly to see how you can forge a relationship going forward through multiple events.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-total-revenue\">Total revenue</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This metric refers to all of the money that your event brought in for you or the organization.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-it-helps-8\">How it helps</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This number gives a high-level overview of what the event contributed monetarily to the organization.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can subtract your total costs from your revenue to find your profit. For example, If ticket sales are the revenue driver, then you’ll take your total ticket sales revenue minus total event cost to find your net profits.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-to-track-this-6\">How to track this</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Calculate all of your ticket sales, merchandise, donations, and so on earned from your event and track them in a spreadsheet.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For a detailed look at revenue and profit, you can also include estimated or exact value for new customers, depending on your product/service sales cycle.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-testimonials\">Testimonials</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>These are the blurbs or stories that event attendees share with you after the event ends that give a glimpse on what it was like to attend the event.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-it-helps-9\">How it helps</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Testimonials provide first-hand experiences from participants on what the event did for them. Make sure to grab testimonials from your speakers, sponsors, and attendees to see a well-rounded view of your event.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-to-track-this-7\">How to track this</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Reach out directly and ask for testimonials. You can do this in an email follow-up, on social media, as a survey question, or in direct asks. The more personal and heartfelt your request, the more likely attendees may be to gush about you – especially if they had a fabulous time.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-how-to-use-event-metrics-nbsp\">How to use event metrics&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With these numbers in hand, now you can use your data to your advantage in several ways. Here are some of the best ways to turn your metrics into shareable results:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-measure-event-roi-nbsp\">Measure event ROI&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Your event ROI will depend on your event goals plus the corresponding KPI. For example, to track your ROI on attendance, you’ll calculate:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Total attendees ÷ Total registrations x 100&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>This could look something like 1000 attendees ÷ 1500 registrations x 100 = 66%. This lets you know that two thirds of registrations actually attended the event.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are a number of ways you can set goals that are specific to your event. In fact, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/defining-event-goals-and-objectives/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">defining event goals and objectives</a> should be one of the very first things you do in event planning! </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-create-an-event-report-nbsp\">Create an event report&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Essential metrics can go right into a nice event report that can then be shared with stakeholders and other interested folks. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/how-to-manage-analytics-and-reporting-for-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Reporting is important for any event</a> as it’s a place to gather all of your data and prepare for future events. The best part is that it can be done easily with The Events Calendar. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re using <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets Plus</a> as well, you can also add custom fields to capture additional information about your attendees. You can also track your <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/tracking-sales-and-payments-with-event-tickets-plus/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ticket sales and payments</a> by hovering over the Orders tab where you edit your events. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-improve-your-future-events-nbsp\">Improve your future events&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Event metrics can paint a picture of what others thought of your event and your brand. A good metric to track here is event engagement. Pay attention to the metrics that show how excited attendees were about the topics, agenda, and speakers; this is often tracked in post-event surveys or in social media comments.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Remember that both good and bad results are important to look at. Both can inform future events and create a baseline for comparison to see if you can meet or exceed this engagement level at the next event.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-exploring-event-metrics-with-the-events-calendar-nbsp\">Exploring event metrics with The Events Calendar&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Event metrics are crucial to understanding how your event performed and if you achieved a positive ROI. Metrics empower you to quantitatively measure your event’s success, demonstrate tangible value, and validate your overall event marketing strategy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Tracking a lot of metrics may seem like busy work, but it’s made easy with tools like The Events Calendar and Event Tickets. With <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Event Tickets Plus</a>, you can also capture event metrics right in your WordPress dashboard and create helpful reports. Some of the metrics you can track with Event Tickets Plus include total check-ins, total tickets issued/sold, and attendee information. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://demo.theeventscalendar.com/request-demo-site/\">Try out Event Tickets Plus on a demo site </a>to see if these features are what you’ve been looking for. With power like this, all on WordPress, you’ll be prepared for your next successful event!</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/event-metrics/\">The Ultimate Guide to KPIs for Event ROI</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"How to Track Attendance at Events (In-person, Virtual, and Hybrid)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:140:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/how-to-track-attendance-at-events/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 09 Dec 2024 15:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Event Management\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2546893\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:673:\"<p>Tired of wrestling with paper sign-in sheets and spending hours manually counting attendees? If you&#8217;re still tracking event attendance the old-fashioned way, you&#8217;re likely dealing with missing data, counting errors, and precious time going to waste. Modern-day event management is anything but simple. Whether you&#8217;re running in-person meetups, virtual workshops, or those hybrid events that&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/how-to-track-attendance-at-events/\">How to Track Attendance at Events (In-person, Virtual, and Hybrid)</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Alexis\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30219:\"\n<p>Tired of wrestling with paper sign-in sheets and spending hours manually counting attendees? If you&#8217;re still tracking event attendance the old-fashioned way, you&#8217;re likely dealing with missing data, counting errors, and precious time going to waste.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Modern-day event management is anything but simple. Whether you&#8217;re running in-person meetups, virtual workshops, or those hybrid events that give attendees the best of both worlds, each format brings its own attendance tracking challenges.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But don&#8217;t worry — this guide will walk you through the digital solutions that make tracking attendance a breeze. Ready to make the switch to modern attendance tracking? Let’s go!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-understanding-event-attendance-tracking\"><strong>Understanding event attendance tracking</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Event attendance tracking is a smart way to understand exactly who&#8217;s showing up and how they&#8217;re engaging with your event.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Different event formats need different tracking approaches. For in-person events, you&#8217;ll want to monitor entry points, track movement between sessions, and see which areas draw the biggest crowds. Virtual events are all about tracking those login times, session views, and how people interact in chat rooms or Q&amp;As.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And hybrid events? They&#8217;re extra exhausting…err, sorry…<em>exciting</em> because you&#8217;re tracking both physical and online attendance at the same time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Is all of this challenging? Sure. But is it worth it? Absolutely!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-the-benefits-of-attendance-tracking\"><strong>The benefits of attendance tracking</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Good attendance tracking transforms how you run events. Here&#8217;s what you can achieve with the right tracking system in place:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Measure real success and ROI: </strong>Want to know exactly how successful your event was? Tracking gives you concrete numbers on attendance, engagement levels, and participation patterns. No more guessing about ROI — you&#8217;ll have real data to show the value of every event.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Make smarter planning decisions: </strong>When you know which sessions drew the biggest crowds and what content resonated most, planning your next event becomes much clearer. Use attendance insights to refine your event strategy and create programs your attendees will love.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Create better experiences: </strong>Understanding how people interact with your event helps you personalize their experience. From registration to session selection, you can customize everything based on real participation patterns and feedback.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stay flexible with real-time insights: </strong>Need to open another registration desk? Add more seating to a popular session? Good tracking lets you make smart adjustments on the fly, keeping your event running smoothly.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Impress your stakeholders: </strong>Sponsors and stakeholders love seeing concrete results. With detailed tracking data, you can show them exactly how their investment paid off through comprehensive performance reports.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Keep everything secure and efficient: </strong>From managing venue capacity to ensuring smooth check-ins, proper tracking helps you run safer, more efficient events. It&#8217;s your behind-the-scenes superpower for operations management.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Modern tracking tools make all this possible without the headache of manual counting or complicated spreadsheets. They turn your attendance data into actionable insights that help you improve every aspect of your events.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-traditional-manual-methods-for-check-in-and-attendance-tracking\"><strong>Traditional manual methods for check-in and attendance tracking</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a moment to look at traditional event attendance tracking methods (and why they might be holding you back):</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Physical tickets and badges:</strong> Sure, they&#8217;re familiar, but they&#8217;re also a hassle. They get lost, they can be copied, and checking them manually creates those dreaded entry lines. Plus, you&#8217;ll spend hours sorting through stubs after the event.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Swipe cards:</strong> These seemed high-tech once, but they come with their own problems. Attendees forget them, lose them, or sometimes even share them. Not to mention the panic when the card reader decides to take an unexpected break!</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Printed lists and sign-in sheets:</strong> We&#8217;ve all been there — flipping through pages of names while a line grows longer and longer. These lists become messy and get outdated quickly, and good luck trying to read everyone&#8217;s handwriting!</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Excel spreadsheets:</strong> They&#8217;re better than paper, but not by much. Manual data entry is slow and prone to typos, and you can&#8217;t update them in real-time across your team. Plus, trying to analyze data later? That&#8217;s a whole other challenge.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Clicker counters:</strong> Click, click, click&#8230; but what happens when someone walks out and back in? Or when your counter gets stuck? You might know how many people came through, but you won&#8217;t know who they were or where they went.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>More often than not, these methods lead to long queues, frustrated attendees, and inaccurate data. Modern digital solutions, on the other hand, offer real-time insights and integrate smoothly with event management tools, addressing these inefficiencies.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-using-effective-digital-tools-for-tracking-in-person-events\"><strong>Using effective digital tools for tracking in-person events</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that we&#8217;ve covered what doesn&#8217;t work, let&#8217;s dive into what does! There are some brilliant options on the market for both novice and tech-savvy event managers that can transform your check-in process.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-simple-digital-tickets-qr-codes-and-mobile-apps\"><strong>Simple: Digital tickets, QR codes, and mobile apps</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s look at some basic digital tools that are still quite powerful.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Digital tickets: </strong>Say goodbye to printing and mailing physical tickets. Digital tickets go straight to attendees&#8217; phones, eliminating lost tickets and fraud concerns. They&#8217;re easy to resend, impossible to duplicate, and always within reach.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>QR codes: </strong>Each ticket comes with a <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/event-qr-codes/\">unique QR code that&#8217;s scannable in seconds</a> using any smartphone or tablet. It&#8217;s a contactless, quick solution that keeps entry lines moving smoothly. Plus, every scan automatically updates your attendance data.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Mobile apps:</strong> Track arrivals in real-time, work offline when needed, and sync data automatically when you&#8217;re back online. Many apps connect directly with your WordPress site through <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/wordpress-event-management-plugin/\">simple event management plugins</a>, making setup painless.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The beauty of these tools? They&#8217;re simple to implement but deliver impressive results. You&#8217;ll get accurate attendance data, happy attendees, and none of the usual check-in headaches.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-advanced-self-service-kiosks-rfid-and-facial-recognition\"><strong>Advanced: Self-service kiosks, RFID, and facial recognition</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Looking for high-tech solutions? These advanced options pack some serious power — but with trade-offs:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Self-service kiosks:</strong> Perfect for large events, these stations let attendees check themselves in quickly. While they&#8217;re great for reducing lines and staff needs, they require significant upfront investment and technical setup.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>RFID technology:</strong> These smart badges track movement throughout your venue and provide incredible attendance insights. But the hardware costs add up, and you&#8217;ll need technical expertise to manage the system.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Facial recognition:</strong> The newest kid on the block offers touchless check-in and enhanced security. However, it&#8217;s expensive, raises privacy concerns, and requires careful implementation.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>While these solutions are impressive, they might be more than most events need. For most organizers, the simpler digital options we covered earlier will do the job perfectly at a fraction of the cost and complexity.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-tracking-attendance-in-virtual-and-hybrid-events\"><strong>Tracking attendance in virtual and hybrid events</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When some (or all) of your attendees are joining from their screens, attendance tracking needs a different approach. Let&#8217;s look at the most effective methods:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Smart RSVP tracking:</strong> It starts before your event begins. Collect detailed registration data to set your baseline, then track how many people actually show up. This helps you measure attendance rates and plan future events better.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Virtual session monitoring:</strong> Platforms like <a href=\"https://www.zoom.com/\">Zoom</a> provide powerful tracking features. You&#8217;ll see who joined, how long they stayed, and when they left. Plus, you&#8217;ll get detailed reports showing engagement levels throughout your sessions.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Engagement tracking:</strong> Don&#8217;t just count logins; measure real participation through chat activity, poll responses, and Q&amp;A involvement. This tells you who just showed up and who actually engaged with your content.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Hybrid event management:</strong> Running both in-person and virtual components? Use a single system (like <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/\">The Events Calendar</a>) to track everyone. This gives you a complete view of attendance across both formats without jumping between different tools.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Want to verify your numbers? Send out post-event surveys. They&#8217;ll confirm who attended and also give you valuable feedback to make your next event even better.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-choose-the-events-calendar-for-comprehensive-attendance-management\"><strong>Choose The Events Calendar for comprehensive attendance management</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Looking for a solution that handles all the attendance tracking methods we&#8217;ve discussed? <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/\">The Events Calendar</a> and <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets Plus</a> bring everything together in one powerful package. From intimate workshops to large-scale conferences, this power duo transforms complicated attendance tracking into a streamlined process.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-unified-ticketing-and-registration\"><strong>Unified ticketing and registration</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Juggling multiple systems for event and ticket management is ancient history. The Events Calendar and Event Tickets Plus give you <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/build-a-ticketing-website/\">one central hub for all your ticketing needs</a>. You can:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Create different ticket types for both in-person and virtual attendees.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"596\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-665x596.png\" alt=\"Standard ticket creation dashboard and alternative ticket types \" class=\"wp-image-2546900\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-665x596.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-300x269.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-95x85.png 95w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-768x688.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-430x385.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-645x578.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-1068x957.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-460x412.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-1074x963.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-512x459.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-1230x1102.png 1230w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-591x530.png 591w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-600x538.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type-500x448.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-type.png 1398w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Manage all registrations through one clean, organized dashboard.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"525\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-665x525.png\" alt=\"Attendee registration and ticket management settings\" class=\"wp-image-2546899\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-665x525.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-300x237.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-108x85.png 108w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-768x607.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-430x340.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-645x510.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-1068x844.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-460x363.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-1074x849.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-512x405.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-1395x1102.png 1395w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-671x530.png 671w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-600x474.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings-500x395.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/ticket-settings.png 1472w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Track sales and attendance data in real time.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Build excitement by <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/public-attendee-list/\">displaying attendee lists</a> on your event page.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Keep everything organized with automatic data sorting.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-customizable-registration-fields-for-targeted-data-collection\"><strong>Customizable registration fields for targeted data collection</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Want to know more about your attendees? Custom registration fields let you gather exactly the information you need:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Create specific questions for different ticket types.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Collect dietary preferences for in-person events.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Learn about content preferences for virtual sessions.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Understand attendee experience levels.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Gather session preferences for better planning.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"510\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-665x510.png\" alt=\"Custom registration fields you can add to your ticket registration form\" class=\"wp-image-2546898\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-665x510.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-300x230.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-111x85.png 111w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-768x589.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-1536x1178.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-430x330.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-645x495.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-1068x819.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-460x353.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-1602x1228.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-1074x823.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-512x393.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-1611x1235.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-1437x1102.png 1437w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-691x530.png 691w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-600x460.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields-500x383.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/custom-registration-fields.png 1852w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All this data helps you create more personalized experiences. Use the information to send targeted communications, recommend relevant sessions, and make each attendee feel like the event was designed just for them.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-real-time-check-in-and-monitoring\"><strong>Real-time check-in and monitoring</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>With Event Tickets Plus, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/qr-code-for-ticket-validation/\">every ticket comes with a unique QR code</a> that attendees can store right in their phone&#8217;s virtual wallet — no more paper tickets to lose or forget. Plus, for in-person events, you get:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Lightning-fast QR code scanning for instant check-ins.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Simple manual check-in options when needed.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Real-time attendance tracking from your dashboard.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Automatic attendance status updates.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Quick access to attendee information.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Virtual events? We&#8217;ve got those covered, too. Direct integration with Zoom means you&#8217;ll track online attendance automatically, giving you clear insight into engagement across all your event formats.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"670\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-665x670.png\" alt=\"Configuring virtual and hybrid events\" class=\"wp-image-2546897\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-665x670.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-298x300.png 298w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-84x85.png 84w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-768x774.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-430x433.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-645x650.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-180x180.png 180w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-1068x1076.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-460x464.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-1074x1082.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-512x516.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-1093x1102.png 1093w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-526x530.png 526w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-600x605.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events-500x504.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/configure-virtual-hybrid-events.png 1413w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-advanced-reporting-and-analytics\"><strong>Advanced reporting and analytics</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Keep track of your event&#8217;s success with easy-to-access sales and attendance data. Right from your WordPress dashboard, you can:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/tracking-sales-and-payments-with-event-tickets-plus/\">Monitor ticket sales</a> and revenue through the Orders tab.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Export attendee information to CSV files for detailed analysis.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Track different ticket types and their performance.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>View attendance lists and check-in status.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Access payment information and purchase details.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"295\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-665x295.png\" alt=\"Event orders tracking page\" class=\"wp-image-2546896\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-665x295.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-300x133.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-140x62.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-768x340.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-1536x681.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-2048x908.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-430x191.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-645x286.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-2000x886.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-1068x473.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-460x204.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-1602x710.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-1074x476.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-512x227.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-1611x714.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-707x313.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-600x266.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/12/event-orders-page-500x222.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Want to dig deeper? Create custom event reports to track your key performance indicators (KPIs). Combine your ticket data with post-event surveys and attendance feedback to make informed decisions for future events. Plus, you can easily export all this information to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/how-to-manage-analytics-and-reporting-for-events/\">manage in your preferred analysis tools</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-flexible-integration-with-other-tools\"><strong>Flexible integration with other tools</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Your event management shouldn&#8217;t exist in a vacuum. That&#8217;s why we&#8217;ve built robust integration capabilities into The Events Calendar. Connect with <a href=\"https://zapier.com/\">Zapier</a> to automate your workflows, sync data with your favorite CRM, and keep your marketing tools in the loop.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Key integration features include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Hassle-free Zapier connections.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Automatic data synchronization.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Marketing tool integration.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Custom API access.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Flexible automation options.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-why-choose-the-events-calendar\"><strong>Why choose The Events Calendar?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Events Calendar and Event Tickets Plus create a powerhouse solution right in your WordPress dashboard. You get all the tools you need to manage events of any size or format, plus the confidence of working with a trusted platform used by thousands of event planners worldwide.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Moreover, our premium support team is always ready to help you succeed. From setup assistance to advanced feature guidance, you&#8217;ll have expert help every step of the way.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-common-challenges-in-attendance-tracking\"><strong>Common challenges in attendance tracking</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Even with the best tools, attendance tracking isn&#8217;t always smooth sailing. Let&#8217;s tackle the most common challenges and their solutions head-on:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-getting-accurate-data\"><strong>Getting accurate data</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Ever notice how your registration numbers don&#8217;t match actual attendance? It&#8217;s a common frustration. Some people register but don&#8217;t show up, while others might attend only part of your event.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The fix? Use digital tools that track actual attendance:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>QR code scanning for precise check-ins.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Automated virtual attendance monitoring.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Real-time tracking across all sessions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-managing-multiple-event-formats\"><strong>Managing multiple event formats</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Running hybrid events means tracking both in-person and virtual attendees simultaneously. This can quickly become overwhelming without the right system in place.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The solution is using a unified platform that handles both:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Track all attendance types in one dashboard.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Monitor engagement across formats.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Keep data organized and accessible.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-handling-technical-hiccups\"><strong>Handling technical hiccups</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ve all been there — the internet drops during check-in, or the virtual platform has issues. These technical problems can throw off your entire tracking system.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Be prepared with:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Backup check-in methods.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Offline tracking capabilities.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Quick access to technical support.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-protecting-attendee-privacy\"><strong>Protecting attendee privacy</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>With great data comes great responsibility. Collecting attendee information means you need to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/data-privacy/\">handle it carefully and comply with privacy regulations</a> like <a href=\"https://gdpr-info.eu/\">GDPR</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure you&#8217;re:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Using GDPR-compliant tools.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Collecting only necessary information.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Storing data securely.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Being transparent about data usage.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-making-sense-of-your-data\"><strong>Making sense of your data</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Having numbers is one thing; knowing what they mean is another. Turn your attendance data into valuable insights by:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Setting clear success metrics before your event.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Comparing patterns across multiple events.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Using post-event surveys to get the full picture.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Analyzing engagement levels and session popularity.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Every challenge has a solution. With the right tools and preparation, you can turn these common hurdles into opportunities for better event management.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-improve-your-events-with-effective-attendance-tracking\"><strong>Improve your events with effective attendance tracking</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Great events are never a fluke. They&#8217;re built on data and insights from previous experiences. With proper attendance tracking, you&#8217;ll understand exactly what works and what needs improvement.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/bundles/starter-bundle/\">The Events Calendar and Event Tickets Plus</a> give you all the tools you need to gather this valuable information. From registration patterns to check-in data, every insight helps you create better experiences for your attendees.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to transform your events? Start by implementing these attendance tracking strategies with The Events Calendar!</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/how-to-track-attendance-at-events/\">How to Track Attendance at Events (In-person, Virtual, and Hybrid)</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:35:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application